                             DecodeResult result)
                      throws DecoderException

        Parameters:

        result - - DecodeResult structure
        Throws:

      • waitMultipleDecode

        public void waitMultipleDecode(int dwTimeout)
                        throws DecoderException
        This function is used to read multiple symbols using a single function call. When called, this function attempts to find and decode unique symbols once, and use the callbackMultiRead() function to notify the application data is available. This function continues to find and decode symbols until the time specified in the dwTimeout parameter has expired, or until one of the callbackKeepGoing() functions returns false.
        Parameters:
        dwTimeout - - length of time in milliseconds to timeout
        Throws:
        DecoderException

      • callbackKeepGoing

        public boolean callbackKeepGoing()
        Callback used to stop decoding. It is used in conjunction with waitForDecode(int), waitForDecodeTwo(int, DecodeResult) and waitMultipleDecode(int).
        Returns:
        true if the Decoder should continue looking for symbols, otherwise false to stop the decode process.

      • callbackMultiRead

        public boolean callbackMultiRead()
        Callback used for MultiRead (Shotgun). Upon successful decode when using waitMultipleDecode(int), the API calls this function when data is available and can be retrieved.
        Returns:
        true if the Decoder is to continue to look for additional symbols, otherwise return false to stop decode attempts.
